/*
whenever we're working with files we must use try-catch block to handle possilbe IO Execptions. 
Two modes for writing - write and append
    Write Mode:
        1. if file doesn't exist, Java will create it and write the contents to it
        2. if it does, java will overwrite contents of file with new content
    Append Mode:
        1. if file doesn't exist, java will create it and write contents to it
        2. if file exists, java write new contents to the file after the existing contents
    Classes for writing: PrintWriter and FileWriter
    Reading from a file
        file you want to red from must exist prior
        file you are trying to read from doesn't exist, will get FileNotFoundException
        classes for reading: Scanner and File
*/